OL,6,FCrawley, of Sheehan Crescent,
OL,7,FCarlisle, had tried to murder the
OL,8,Fsecond man with a hammer near York on
OL,9,FJanuary 5 after skipping bail and
OL,10,Ftravelling first to Glasgow, Aberdeen
OL,11,Fand Edinburgh.
OL,13,FThe man suffered a head wound, was
OL,14,F"haunted" by the attack and stated: "I
OL,15,Fhonestly think that if I hadn't
OL,16,Fmanaged to escape I would have ended
OL,17,Fup dead, just like the other man
OL,18,Fbefore me, and this thought
OL,19,Fcontinually goes around in my mind."
